$ VBA: optional parameters

The keyword → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters/keyword-optional[`optional`] declares a function/sub parameter to be optional.

The function → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/optional-parameters/keyword-isMissing[`isMissing`] can be used to check if a value was specified for an optional parameter.

The keyword → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/parameters/paramArray[`paramArray`] allows to pass an aribtrary number of arguments to a sub or function.

sa:
  → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/parameters[Sub and function parameters]
